Book Title: Grimms' Fairy Tales

Book Author: Jacob Grimm

Paragraph: (1) Once there was a woman whose husband told her she needed to work or they would have no food. (2) She started selling things at the market. (3) She was so pretty that people would buy things from her without even taking them.

 (4) They did this for a while until one day, a soldier rode his horse into her stall and broke everything. (5) The woman was very upset and didn't know what to do. (6) She ran home to tell her husband. (7) He was disappointed and told her that selling at the market was not a good job for her.

 (8) Instead, her husband found her a job at the king’s palace as a kitchen maid. (9) She helped the cook with all the hardest jobs but got to bring home some leftover food.

 (10) While working at the palace, she heard that the king’s son was getting married. (11) She peeked out of the window to see the grand event. (12) She felt sad about how her choices had changed her life so much.

 (13) One day, the king’s son walked in wearing golden clothes. (14) He saw the woman and asked her to dance. (15) She was scared because she knew he was making fun of her. (16) As they danced, the food from her basket fell out, and everyone laughed.

 (17) She tried to leave, but the king's son stopped her. (18) He told her not to be afraid. (19) He said he was the fiddler who had lived with her before and even the soldier who broke her stall. (20) He explained that he did all that because he loved her and wanted her to see how her pride was not good.

 (21) He had hoped to teach her a lesson. (22) Now that she had learned it, he said it was time for them to get married.



