Paragraph: (1) "But Sir," Gregor called out, "I will open the door very soon. (2) Just a second. (3) I feel a bit dizzy and couldn't get out of bed until now. (4) I am still lying here but don't worry, I’m feeling better. (5) I am getting up right now. (6) Please be patient with me. (7) It’s a bit harder than I thought to get up when you feel dizzy. (8) But, I’m okay now, really. (9) It's strange how quickly someone can feel sick! (10) I was fine last night, and my parents knew I had a small sign of feeling unwell then. (11) They must have noticed something was off. (12) I should have told you earlier at work! (13) Sometimes, we think we can get through the day without staying home when we're sick. (14) Please don't upset my parents! (15) There’s really no reason for anyone to be making accusations. (16) Maybe you missed the latest reports I sent in. (17) I plan to catch the eight o'clock train after resting a bit more. (18) You don’t have to wait for me, sir; I'll come to the office shortly after you. (19) Could you please let the boss know that? (20) While saying all this, Gregor tried to get out of bed. (21) He moved towards his chest of drawers, which he reached quite easily, maybe because he had tried a few times already. (22) He really wanted to open the door to talk to the chief clerk and show himself. (23) The others outside were insisting a lot, and Gregor was eager to see their reaction when they saw him. (24) If they were shocked, it wouldn't be his fault anymore, and he could relax. (25) But if they were okay with it, he wouldn’t need to worry, and he could still make it to his train at eight.

 (26) At first, Gregor kept slipping when he tried to climb the smooth chest of drawers, but after one big push, he managed to stand upright. (27) His lower body hurt a lot, but he ignored the pain. (28) Then, he leaned against a chair and held on tight with his legs. (29) After a while, he calmed down and stayed quiet to hear what the chief clerk was saying outside.

 (30) "Did you understand any of that?". (31) the chief clerk asked Gregor's parents, doubtful of Gregor’s words. (32) "Oh, God!". (33) Gregor’s mom cried out, already crying, "He might be really sick, and we are just making it worse. (34) Grete! (35) Grete!". (36) she called for his sister. (37) "Mother?". (38) Grete replied from across the room. (39) They talked through the room, worried. (40) "You need to get the doctor right away. (41) Gregor is sick. (42) Hurry, call the doctor. (43) Did you hear how strange Gregor sounded?". (44) "That sounded like an animal," the chief clerk remarked calmly, contrasting with his mother's worried cries.

 (45) "Anna! (46) Anna!". (47) Gregor’s father shouted towards the kitchen, clapping his hands, "We need a locksmith now!". (48) The two girls, Grete and her mother, quickly ran through the hall, their skirts swishing, and flung open the front door. (49) Gregor wondered how his sister got ready so fast. (50) The door didn’t slam shut; it stayed open. (51) Sometimes, doors stay open in houses where something unexpected has happened.



