Book Title: Great Expectations

Book Author: Charles Dickens

Paragraph: (1) One day, a boy named Pip was sitting with Miss Havisham and Estella in a big, old house. (2) As the candles slowly burned lower, Miss Havisham stared into the fireplace for a long time. (3) Suddenly, some red coals collapsed with a small noise, and she looked towards Pip again. (4) Estella kept knitting calmly while all of this was happening.

 (5) Miss Havisham broke the silence and asked Pip, "What else?".

 (6) Pip turned to Estella and said, trying to keep his voice steady, “Estella, you know I love you. (7) You know I’ve loved you for a very long time.”

Estella looked up at Pip while she continued knitting, but her face didn’t show any feelings. (8) Pip noticed that Miss Havisham was watching them both carefully.

